<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ The additive identity for $𝗤$ is $\eqc{(0_{𝗭}, 1_{𝗭})}$. ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ The multiplicative identity for $𝗭$ is $\eqc{(1_{𝗭}, 1_{𝗭})}$. ⦉
</statement>

§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the additive identity of $𝗤$ by $0_{𝗤}$ and the
    multiplicative identity by $1_{𝗤}$. ⦉

  ‖ We denote the set $\Set{q ∈ 𝗤}{q ≥ 0_{Q}}$ by $𝗤_{+}$. ⦉
⦉

